# pyenv
#   For a library or app, you might want to share your .python-version.
#   Reference: https://github.com/pyenv/pyenv/blob/master/COMMANDS.md#pyenv-version-file
#.python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if delegates have different OS, lock file shall be ignored.
#Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Using poetry.lock is recommended in projects, but let's allow it or not. We keep lock files.
# poetry.lock

# pdm
#   PDM stores project-wide configurations in .pdm.toml
.pdm.toml
.pdm-plugins/
__pdm-build/

# PEP 582; used by e.g. github.com/lincolnloop/layman and pdm
__pfx__/

